<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- Key Bb (2 flats). Modal feel — Gm tonic (i in Bb). LH open voicings on strong beats.
- Gm: G2-D3-G3-Bb3; Dm: D2-A2-D3-F3; Bb: Bb2-F3-Bb3-D4; Eb: Eb2-Bb2-Eb3-G3.
- Extended harmonies (EbΔ7, Gm7, Cm7) used for Irish chorale color.
- RH: Light 2-note thirds throughout, mirroring the modal simplicity.

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- Gm-Dm-Bb-F-C cycles provide clear diatonic motion in Bb major key area.
- Common tones D and F sustained between Gm/Dm/Bb chords.
- Bars 9-11: Eb major section provides IV-area contrast before returning to Gm.

TEXTURE ARC:
- Opening: Sparse pickup to full Gm, building through Dm-Bb sequence.
- Middle (bars 9-12): Lush EbΔ7 + Gm7 harmonies, climax bar 12-13.
- Closing (14-16): Return to Gm tonic, final single beat.
-->
